@emersonmanning6523 The Moab Utah Police report from August 12, 2021, details a domestic disturbance incident involving Gabby Petito and Brian Laundrie. According to the report, Petito had visible injuries, including marks on her arm and face. Laundrie, on the other hand, had no visible injuries reported.

During the police stop, Petito told officers that Laundrie had grabbed her face, causing an injury. Laundrie's account differed, claiming Petito was the aggressor and that he was trying to calm her down.

It's worth noting that neither Petito nor Laundrie wanted to press charges, and the police ultimately characterized the incident as a "mental breakdown" rather than domestic violence.

